messages.messageBody:
How funny! I no longer think of pink poodles when I hear FiFi ( Feefee) but
it actualy fits our Ethan quite well, too! He's got the sassy attitude and
charm as well. And these beautiful long eyelashes and sparkling brown eyes
to match! For a little boy who couldn't be any more BOY, he's also a
prancer and just bounces on air when he walks. Maybe a male French
Poodle??? LOL

My best friend has three kids and calls them poopers, bobo and teetee. They
started out as Carly-Poo, Adam-Bo-Badum and Leah-Weah. Leah's eventually
became we-we, then progressed on to teetee. Don't ask me why but those all
stuck and I figure I'll tell Ethan it could be worse! Haha!
Jennifer
>
>My DD Fiona is often called "Fifi". When she was first born my DS (then
>2) crowned her Princess Fiona / Fifi. I thought I'd totally hate having
>a Fifi (because of the French poodle thing;) but she totally wears the
>name. She's got this great sassy attitude and tons charm to pull it
>off. She's definitely a Fifi. ;)
>
>TreeGoddess
